Scientists from Cambridge University and Oxford Brookes University say Neanderthals may have succumbed to infectious diseases carried to Europe by modern humans as they migrated out of Africa . 
  Evidence suggests they would have been infected by tuberculosis, typhoid and the common cold . 
  Anthropologists say modern humans may have been able to cope with these diseases but NeanderthALS could not . 
  They say Neanderthal genes may have made us more vulnerable to cancer and diabetes . 
 